      "content": "i feel like the \"structural flaws\" argument gets brushed aside a lot in mainstream stuff though. like, if the veto power in the security council basically makes it impossible to act whenever a big power is involved, isn't that a permanent feature that makes the whole thing kind of a sham for maintaining peace? do most experts actually consider that a legitimate way to run a global organization, or is it seen as a major dealbreaker?",
